    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>You need to set it in the value itself, not in the prepared statement SQL string. </p>\n\n<p>So, this should do for a prefix-match:</p>\n\n<pre><code>notes = notes\n    .replace(\"!\", \"!!\")\n    .replace(\"%\", \"!%\")\n    .replace(\"_\", \"!_\")\n    .replace(\"[\", \"![\");\nPreparedStatement pstmt = con.prepareStatement(\n        \"SELECT * FROM analysis WHERE notes LIKE ? ESCAPE '!'\");\npstmt.setString(1, notes + \"%\");\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>or a suffix-match:</p>\n\n<pre><code>pstmt.setString(1, \"%\" + notes);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>or a global match:</p>\n\n<pre><code>pstmt.setString(1, \"%\" + notes + \"%\");\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
